  "prompt": "Can I use digital locker facility to sign my documents using Aadhar verification and use it in place of e-mudhra digital signature?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, you can't use the Digital Locker facility to directly sign documents using Aadhaar verification as an equivalent to an e-Mudhra digital signature.\n\nDigital Locker is primarily designed to store and securely share government-issued documents digitally. While it offers a secure space to keep and share documents, it does not inherently provide the functionality to digitally sign documents using Aadhaar.\n\ne-Mudhra, on the other hand, is a certified authority that provides digital signature certificates in India. These certificates allow you to sign documents electronically in accordance with the Information Technology Act, 2000, which ensures legal validity.\n\nFor signing documents digitally with legal standing, you should use digital signatures issued by certified authorities like e-Mudhra. Some providers may allow digital signatures using Aadhaar-based verification, but this functionality would typically be provided through a specific service designed for that purpose, not simply through Digital Locker. \n\nTo digitally sign a document with legal validity, you will need to obtain a digital signature certificate from a licensed Certifying Authority like e-Mudhra.",
